<% layout('./base') %>

  <form action="/shortenbrowser" method="POST">
    <label class="field">
      <input type="text" name="longUrl" />
      <span class="label">Enter URL</span>
    </label>
    <input type="submit" class="button custombutton" value="Shorten!" />
  </form>

  <br />
  <div class="fs-small">
    <p>This is an example of a link shortening microservice.</p>
    <p>You can find the source code on <a class="-link" href="https://github.com/tusharpandey13/node-elastic-beanstalk">github</a></p>

    <p>
    <img src="/system.jpg"/>
    </p>

    <li>It is made using <a class="-link" href="https://nodejs.org/">NodeJS</a> and <a class="-link"
        href="https://expressjs.com/">ExpressJS</a></li>
    <li>It uses <a class="-link" href="https://www.mongodb.com/">MongoDB</a> as document store</li>
    <li>It uses <a class="-link" href="https://redis.io/">Redis</a> as caching layer</li>
    <li>It is deployed automatically on <a class="-link" href="https://aws.amazon.com/elasticbeanstalk/">AWS Elastic
        Beanstalk</a> using <a class="-link" href="https://github.com/features/actions">Github Actions</a> CI/CD</li>
    <li>An api is also exposed for the same. The API documentation can be found <a class="-link" href="https://documenter.getpostman.com/view/9368565/TzkyNLWL">here</a></li>
  </div>